20/08/2003
BIHAC, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Deputy SFOR Commander Brig Gen Simon Young mediated a meeting of BiH Army commanders in Bihac on Tuesday (19 August). 
Young told reporters the country would soon have a single army in line with the ongoing restructuring in the two state entities. 
Delegations of the Joint Command of the Federation Army and Republika Srpska Army briefed SFOR staff on the progress achieved so far. 
The meeting also tackled the downsizing plans in the Federation and Republika Srpska armies, as well as measures to reduce the number of weapons warehouses. 
(Onasa, BBC - 19/08/03)
